tika.dc.description: An End of Innocence Meet the wealthy Wilcoxes, the cultured, emancipated Schlegals, and poor, young Bast. Howards End, a house in the countryside, is the source of their conflict-and a symbol of class strife within society, as Forster poses the question of who shall inherit England.
